
🧠 ChatGPT Reviews Analysis
This project analyzes user reviews of ChatGPT to gain insights into user sentiment, behavior, and feedback trends using data visualization and natural language processing (NLP) techniques.

📁 Project Structure
chatgpt_reviews.csv - Dataset containing user reviews and metadata.

ChatGPT Reviews Analysis.ipynb - Jupyter Notebook with complete EDA, preprocessing, sentiment analysis, and visualization.

🔍 Objective
To explore and understand ChatGPT user reviews through:

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Text preprocessing and cleaning

Sentiment analysis using TextBlob and Vader

Word cloud generation and keyword extraction

Visual insights through plots and charts

⚙️ Tools & Technologies
Python (Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn)

NLP Libraries: NLTK, TextBlob, VaderSentiment

Visualization: WordCloud, Plotly

Jupyter Notebook for step-by-step analysis

📊 Key Features
Cleaned and preprocessed real user reviews.

Identified top positive and negative keywords.

Classified reviews into positive, negative, and neutral.

Generated sentiment distribution pie chart.

Created insightful visualizations like word clouds and histograms.

🧪 Sample Insights
Most reviews are overwhelmingly positive.

Common themes include accuracy, creativity, and limitations in responses.

Negative reviews often cite hallucination or incomplete answers.

🚀 How to Run
Clone this repository or download the files.

Open ChatGPT Reviews Analysis.ipynb in Jupyter Notebook or VS Code.

Make sure you have the required libraries installed:

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn nltk textblob vaderSentiment wordcloud
Run all cells to execute the full analysis.

📌 Future Enhancements
Add advanced sentiment classification using pretrained transformer models (BERT, RoBERTa).

Dashboard integration for interactive review exploration.

Time-based trend analysis of sentiments.
